Hi Tennille, 

Sure. Confirming that I've made the updates. 

Here are the links:
https://msbrainbank.org.au/donate-tissue/
https://msbrainbank.org.au/people/

Let us know if you would like further changes.

Hi Rica, Thank you for doing this so quickly. Just a couple of things that need updating:
  • Could you please update the NSW Brain Bank Coordinator to something generic. Maybe just "Coordinator" rather than Associate Professor Michael Buckland (https://msbrainbank.org.au/donate-tissue/)?
  • Could you also please update Dr Julia Morahan's role to Head of Research (https://msbrainbank.org.au/people/)?
I also forgot about the bios for the new people added to https://msbrainbank.org.au/people/. Could you please add these?
  • Danielle Davies: Ms Danielle Davies is part of the team running the MS Australia Brain Bank. Danielle has a Bachelor of Science from the University of Sydney and extensive scientific laboratory experience. As the biobanking scientific officer her responsibilities include database design/management and preserving/preparing MS tissue for characterisation of MS lesions.
  • Andrew Affleck: Mr Andrew Affleck is a Senior Hospital Scientist at RPA Hospital and has built his career around his passion for brain banking. He manages both the MS Research Australia Brain Bank and the Australian Sports Brain Bank. He has more than 10 years' experience in the collection, characterisation, and storing of brain tissue for research, with a focus on neurodegeneration. Andrew brings a wealth of knowledge and expertise to the MS Research Australia Brain Bank, and is committed to continuing efforts to further understand MS and supporting researchers in their efforts to find better treatments and a cure for MS.
  • Gabrielle Ferguson: Ms Gabrielle Ferguson completed a Bachelor of Communications majoring in Political and Social Science at University of Technology Sydney and jumped straight into the non-for-profit world. As well as working and volunteering for several not-for-profits, Gabrielle has assisted in developing her family's growing childcare business over the last 12 years. She has ingratiated herself within the MS research community over the last three years as MS Australia's Grants Coordinator, a duty which she performs alongside her Brain Bank role.
Thank you so much for all your help. Best wishes, Tennille Dr​ Tennille Luker BScAdv(Hons), PhD Research Coordinator MS Australia/MS Research Australia 02 8413 7904 • 1300 356 467 tluker@msra.org.au • www.msra.org.au Level 19 Northpoint • 100 Miller Street • North Sydney NSW 2060 [url=fax:Working%20Days:%20Mon-Wed]Working Days: Mon-Wed MS Research Australia is the research arm of MS Australia

Hi Heath,


I hope you're well. I was wondering if it would be possible to update the MSRA Brain Bank website content?


For https://msbrainbank.org.au/donate-tissue/ could you please update these:

For https://msbrainbank.org.au/people/ could you please add a few people?
